A total of 386 patients were identified during the review period (January 2010 to December 2015). Medical records could not be obtained for 4 patients, including 1 patient with vRTI (Figure 1
). The 382 patients reviewed included slightly more males (n = 222; 58.1%) than females (n = 160; 41.9%), and the median patient age was 47 years (interquartile range [IQR], 36 to 56 years). The median age of patients with vRTI was significantly lower than patients without (P = .03). Other patient demographic data and characteristics were not significantly different by vRTI status (Table 1
).
